On Thu, May 11, 2006 at 05:47:05AM -0400, Riad S. Wahby wrote:

> Point of order: it's not at all necessary to use MIME in order to PGP
> sign a message.

Yes, but it's legal (according to RFC2015 or somesuch), and convenient.
It doesn't clutter the mail body, and mutt happens to verify the
signatures automatically. Couldn't get it to verify inline digsigs.
=20
